BROAD-population-type:oth.definition: Individuals were classified as "other" if they did not unambiguously cluster with the specmajor populations (i.e. EUR, NFE, AFR, SAS, EAS and AMR - and ASJ if gnomAD set*) in a principal component analysis (PCA).

GENO:0000134.definition: A DNA marker is present on one copy of a chromosome without a homologous region (e.g., non-PAR portions of the X chromosomes in males; LA6067-9)

GENO:0000135.definition: A DNA marker is present in exactly one copy on two homologous chromosomes (LA6706-1)

GENO:0000136.definition: A DNA marker is present in both copies of homologous chromosomes (LA6705-3)

GENO:0000137.definition: A DNA marker is asserted to be absent

GENO:0000602.definition: A DNA marker is present in all copies of the mitochondrial DNA (LA6704-6)

GENO:0000603.definition: A DNA marker is present in some but not all copies of the mitochondrial DNA (LA6703-8)

GENO:0000882.definition: A DNA marker is present at some level of somatic mosaicism.
